The waters of the world are a vast source,
These rivers, so many paths—flowing,
And soft and formidable, even in change; 
Vast Universe, boundless stretch of the sea—
You wash away my troubles, and in return,
I hear your eternal murmur of whispers.


- Walt Whitman
